{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"If you're here today --"},{"time":2430,"text":"and I'm very happy that you are --"},{"time":4388,"text":"you've all heard about\nhow sustainable development"},{"time":6765,"text":"will save us from ourselves."},{"time":8751,"text":"However, when we're not at TED,\nwe are often told"},{"time":12274,"text":"that a real sustainability policy agenda\nis just not feasible,"},{"time":16207,"text":"especially in large urban areas\nlike New York City."},{"time":19429,"text":"And that's because most people\nwith decision-making powers,"},{"time":22689,"text":"in both the public and the private sector,"},{"time":24943,"text":"really don't feel\nas though they're in danger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27578,"text":"The reason why I'm here today,\nin part, is because of a dog --"},{"time":31695,"text":"an abandoned puppy I found\nback in the rain, back in 1998."},{"time":34997,"text":"She turned out to be\na much bigger dog than I'd anticipated."},{"time":38431,"text":"When she came into my life, we were\nfighting against a huge waste facility"},{"time":42430,"text":"planned for the East River waterfront"},{"time":44916,"text":"despite the fact that\nour small part of New York City"},{"time":47450,"text":"already handled more than 40 percent\nof the entire city's commercial waste:"},{"time":51832,"text":"a sewage treatment pelletizing plant,\na sewage sludge plant, four power plants,"},{"time":57000,"text":"the world's largest\nfood-distribution center,"},{"time":59359,"text":"as well as other industries that bring\nmore than 60,000 diesel truck trips"},{"time":63565,"text":"to the area each week."},{"time":65118,"text":"The area also has one of the lowest ratios\nof parks to people in the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69110,"text":"So when I was contacted\nby the Parks Department"},{"time":71427,"text":"about a $10,000 seed-grant initiative\nto help develop waterfront projects,"},{"time":75609,"text":"I thought they were really\nwell-meaning, but a bit naive."},{"time":78547,"text":"I'd lived in this area all my life,\nand you could not get to the river,"},{"time":82238,"text":"because of all the lovely facilities\nthat I mentioned earlier."},{"time":85555,"text":"Then, while jogging\nwith my dog one morning,"},{"time":87839,"text":"she pulled me into what I thought\nwas just another illegal dump."},{"time":91606,"text":"There were weeds and piles of garbage\nand other stuff that I won't mention here,"},{"time":95407,"text":"but she kept dragging me,"},{"time":96645,"text":"and lo and behold, at the end\nof that lot was the river."},{"time":99541,"text":"I knew that this forgotten\nlittle street-end,"},{"time":101666,"text":"abandoned like the dog that brought\nme there, was worth saving."},{"time":104694,"text":"And I knew it would grow\nto become the proud beginnings"},{"time":107314,"text":"of the community-led revitalization\nof the new South Bronx."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110322,"text":"And just like my new dog, it was an idea\nthat got bigger than I'd imagined."},{"time":114325,"text":"We garnered much support along the way,"},{"time":116484,"text":"and the Hunts Point Riverside Park\nbecame the first waterfront park"},{"time":119668,"text":"that the South Bronx had had\nin more than 60 years."},{"time":122091,"text":"We leveraged that $10,000 seed grant\nmore than 300 times,"},{"time":125481,"text":"into a $3 million park."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127745,"text":"And in the fall, I'm going to exchange\nmarriage vows with my beloved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132697,"text":"(Audience whistles)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":133721,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135013,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":139579,"text":"That's him pressing my buttons\nback there, which he does all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145488,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":148829,"text":"But those of us living\nin environmental justice communities"},{"time":151631,"text":"are the canary in the coal mine."},{"time":153210,"text":"We feel the problems right now,\nand have for some time."},{"time":157290,"text":"Environmental justice, for those of you\nwho may not be familiar with the term,"},{"time":161000,"text":"goes something like this:"},{"time":162224,"text":"no community should be saddled\nwith more environmental burdens"},{"time":165239,"text":"and less environmental benefits\nthan any other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167929,"text":"Unfortunately, race and class\nare extremely reliable indicators"},{"time":172000,"text":"as to where one might find the good stuff,\nlike parks and trees,"},{"time":175061,"text":"and where one might find the bad stuff,\nlike power plants and waste facilities."},{"time":178817,"text":"As a black person in America,\nI am twice as likely as a white person"},{"time":182076,"text":"to live in an area where air pollution\nposes the greatest risk to my health."},{"time":185697,"text":"I am five times more likely\nto live within walking distance"},{"time":188504,"text":"of a power plant or chemical facility,"},{"time":190437,"text":"which I do."},{"time":192149,"text":"These land-use decisions\ncreated the hostile conditions"},{"time":194804,"text":"that lead to problems like obesity,\ndiabetes and asthma."},{"time":197820,"text":"Why would someone leave their home to go\nfor a brisk walk in a toxic neighborhood?"},{"time":201745,"text":"Our 27 percent obesity rate\nis high even for this country,"},{"time":204680,"text":"and diabetes comes with it."},{"time":206117,"text":"One out of four South Bronx\nchildren has asthma."},{"time":208649,"text":"Our asthma hospitalization rate"},{"time":210488,"text":"is seven times higher\nthan the national average."},{"time":212795,"text":"These impacts are coming everyone's way."},{"time":214770,"text":"And we all pay dearly\nfor solid waste costs,"},{"time":217000,"text":"health problems associated\nwith pollution and more odiously,"},{"time":220000,"text":"the cost of imprisoning\nour young black and Latino men,"},{"time":223013,"text":"who possess untold amounts\nof untapped potential."},{"time":225792,"text":"Fifty percent of our residents\nlive at or below the poverty line;"},{"time":228896,"text":"25 percent of us are unemployed."},{"time":230675,"text":"Low-income citizens often use\nemergency-room visits as primary care."},{"time":234722,"text":"This comes at a high cost to taxpayers\nand produces no proportional benefits."},{"time":238645,"text":"Poor people are not only still poor,\nthey are still unhealthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242512,"text":"Fortunately, there are many people\nlike me who are striving for solutions"},{"time":246321,"text":"that won't compromise the lives"},{"time":247845,"text":"of low-income communities of color\nin the short term,"},{"time":250369,"text":"and won't destroy us all in the long term."},{"time":252499,"text":"None of us want that,\nand we all have that in common."},{"time":255009,"text":"So what else do we have in common?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256672,"text":"Well, first of all,\nwe're all incredibly good-looking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259474,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":260685,"text":"Graduated high school, college,\npost-graduate degrees,"},{"time":263496,"text":"traveled to interesting places,\ndidn't have kids in your early teens,"},{"time":266832,"text":"financially stable, never been imprisoned."},{"time":270688,"text":"OK. Good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271872,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":273235,"text":"But, besides being a black woman,"},{"time":274866,"text":"I am different from most of you\nin some other ways."},{"time":277552,"text":"I watched nearly half of the buildings\nin my neighborhood burn down."},{"time":280967,"text":"My big brother Lenny fought in Vietnam,"},{"time":282954,"text":"only to be gunned down\na few blocks from our home."},{"time":288992,"text":"Jesus."},{"time":290271,"text":"I grew up with a crack house\nacross the street."},{"time":294796,"text":"Yeah, I'm a poor black child\nfrom the ghetto."},{"time":298784,"text":"These things make me different from you."},{"time":300975,"text":"But the things we have in common"},{"time":302862,"text":"set me apart from most\nof the people in my community,"},{"time":305625,"text":"and I am in between these two worlds"},{"time":307475,"text":"with enough of my heart\nto fight for justice in the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311315,"text":"So how did things get so different for us?"},{"time":313347,"text":"In the late '40s, my dad --\na Pullman porter, son of a slave --"},{"time":316702,"text":"bought a house in the Hunts Point\nsection of the South Bronx,"},{"time":319593,"text":"and a few years later, he married my mom."},{"time":321632,"text":"At the time, the community was a mostly\nwhite, working-class neighborhood."},{"time":325137,"text":"My dad was not alone."},{"time":326687,"text":"And as others like him pursued\ntheir own version of the American dream,"},{"time":330148,"text":"white flight became common\nin the South Bronx"},{"time":332701,"text":"and in many cities around the country."},{"time":335018,"text":"Red-lining was used by banks,\nwherein certain sections of the city,"},{"time":338675,"text":"including ours, were deemed\noff-limits to any sort of investment."},{"time":342688,"text":"Many landlords believed it was more\nprofitable to torch their buildings"},{"time":346180,"text":"and collect insurance money rather\nthan to sell under those conditions --"},{"time":350375,"text":"dead or injured former tenants\nnotwithstanding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352839,"text":"Hunts Point was formerly\na walk-to-work community,"},{"time":355705,"text":"but now residents had neither\nwork nor home to walk to."},{"time":359655,"text":"A national highway construction boom\nwas added to our problems."},{"time":362865,"text":"In New York State,"},{"time":364040,"text":"Robert Moses spearheaded\nan aggressive highway-expansion campaign."},{"time":367847,"text":"One of its primary goals was\nto make it easier"},{"time":370067,"text":"for residents of wealthy communities\nin Westchester County to go to Manhattan."},{"time":375116,"text":"The South Bronx, which lies in between,\ndid not stand a chance."},{"time":378215,"text":"Residents were often given\nless than a month's notice"},{"time":380789,"text":"before their buildings were razed."},{"time":382443,"text":"600,000 people were displaced."},{"time":384791,"text":"The common perception was"},{"time":386125,"text":"that only pimps and pushers\nand prostitutes were from the South Bronx."},{"time":390000,"text":"And if you are told\nfrom your earliest days"},{"time":392954,"text":"that nothing good is going to come\nfrom your community,"},{"time":395595,"text":"that it's bad and ugly,"},{"time":396770,"text":"how could it not reflect on you?"},{"time":399335,"text":"So now, my family's property\nwas worthless,"},{"time":401877,"text":"save for that it was our home,\nand all we had."},{"time":404543,"text":"And luckily for me, that home\nand the love inside of it,"},{"time":408293,"text":"along with help from teachers, mentors\nand friends along the way, was enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413459,"text":"Now, why is this story important?"},{"time":415172,"text":"Because from a planning perspective,"},{"time":417006,"text":"economic degradation\nbegets environmental degradation,"},{"time":420747,"text":"which begets social degradation."},{"time":423287,"text":"The disinvestment that began\nin the 1960s set the stage"},{"time":426374,"text":"for all the environmental\ninjustices that were to come."},{"time":429000,"text":"Antiquated zoning and land-use\nregulations are still used to this day"},{"time":433000,"text":"to continue putting polluting\nfacilities in my neighborhood."},{"time":436067,"text":"Are these factors taken into consideration\nwhen land-use policy is decided?"},{"time":439869,"text":"What costs are associated\nwith these decisions?"},{"time":442489,"text":"And who pays? Who profits?"},{"time":444749,"text":"Does anything justify\nwhat the local community goes through?"},{"time":448392,"text":"This was \"planning\" -- in quotes --"},{"time":450710,"text":"that did not have\nour best interests in mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453002,"text":"Once we realized that, we decided\nit was time to do our own planning."},{"time":456441,"text":"That small park I told you about earlier"},{"time":458409,"text":"was the first stage of building\na Greenway movement in the South Bronx."},{"time":461711,"text":"I wrote a one-and-a-quarter-million\ndollar federal transportation grant"},{"time":465087,"text":"to design the plan\nfor a waterfront esplanade"},{"time":467219,"text":"with dedicated on-street bike paths."},{"time":468973,"text":"Physical improvements help inform\npublic policy regarding traffic safety,"},{"time":472455,"text":"the placement of the waste\nand other facilities,"},{"time":474724,"text":"which, if done properly, don't compromise\na community's quality of life."},{"time":478220,"text":"They provide opportunities\nto be more physically active,"},{"time":480958,"text":"as well as local economic development."},{"time":483415,"text":"Think bike shops, juice stands."},{"time":485011,"text":"We secured 20 million dollars\nto build first-phase projects."},{"time":487906,"text":"This is Lafayette Avenue --"},{"time":489804,"text":"and that's redesigned\nby Mathews Nielsen Landscape Architects."},{"time":492985,"text":"And once this path is constructed,\nit'll connect the South Bronx"},{"time":496030,"text":"with more than 400 acres\nof Randall's Island Park."},{"time":498403,"text":"Right now we're separated by about 25 feet\nof water, but this link will change that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502401,"text":"As we nurture the natural environment,\nits abundance will give us back even more."},{"time":506689,"text":"We run a project called the Bronx\n[Environmental] Stewardship Training,"},{"time":510524,"text":"which provides job training in the fields\nof ecological restoration,"},{"time":513855,"text":"so that folks from our community\nhave the skills to compete"},{"time":516680,"text":"for these well-paying jobs."},{"time":518043,"text":"Little by little, we're seeding\nthe area with green-collar jobs --"},{"time":521404,"text":"and with people that have both\na financial and personal stake"},{"time":524287,"text":"in their environment."},{"time":525468,"text":"The Sheridan Expressway\nis an underutilized relic"},{"time":528135,"text":"of the Robert Moses era,"},{"time":529358,"text":"built with no regard for the neighborhoods\nthat were divided by it."},{"time":532758,"text":"Even during rush hour,\nit goes virtually unused."},{"time":535551,"text":"The community created\nan alternative transportation plan"},{"time":538247,"text":"that allows for the removal\nof the highway."},{"time":540897,"text":"We have the opportunity now to bring\ntogether all the stakeholders"},{"time":544044,"text":"to re-envision how this 28 acres\ncan be better utilized"},{"time":546656,"text":"for parkland, affordable housing\nand local economic development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549722,"text":"We also built New York City's first green\nand cool roof demonstration project"},{"time":554573,"text":"on top of our offices."},{"time":555985,"text":"Cool roofs are highly-reflective\nsurfaces that don't absorb solar heat,"},{"time":559474,"text":"and pass it on to\nthe building or atmosphere."},{"time":561601,"text":"Green roofs are soil and living plants."},{"time":563657,"text":"Both can be used instead\nof petroleum-based roofing materials"},{"time":566928,"text":"that absorb heat, contribute\nto urban \"heat island\" effect"},{"time":569723,"text":"and degrade under the sun,"},{"time":571072,"text":"which we in turn breathe."},{"time":572318,"text":"Green roofs also retain\nup to 75 percent of rainfall,"},{"time":575000,"text":"so they reduce a city's need to fund\ncostly end-of-pipe solutions --"},{"time":578683,"text":"which, incidentally, are often located"},{"time":580527,"text":"in environmental justice\ncommunities like mine."},{"time":582772,"text":"And they provide habitats\nfor our little friends!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":586096,"text":"[Butterfly]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":587277,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":588524,"text":"So cool!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589731,"text":"Anyway, the demonstration\nproject is a springboard"},{"time":592261,"text":"for our own green roof\ninstallation business,"},{"time":594409,"text":"bringing jobs and sustainable\neconomic activity to the South Bronx."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597935,"text":"[Green is the new black ...]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":599335,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603502,"text":"I like that, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605177,"text":"Anyway, I know Chris told us\nnot to do pitches up here,"},{"time":608897,"text":"but since I have all of your attention:"},{"time":610801,"text":"We need investors. End of pitch."},{"time":612412,"text":"It's better to ask\nfor forgiveness than permission."},{"time":614824,"text":"Anyway --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616004,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":617488,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":622431,"text":"OK. Katrina."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625884,"text":"Prior to Katrina, the South Bronx\nand New Orleans' Ninth Ward"},{"time":628932,"text":"had a lot in common."},{"time":630145,"text":"Both were largely populated\nby poor people of color,"},{"time":632923,"text":"both hotbeds of cultural innovation:\nthink hip-hop and jazz."},{"time":636242,"text":"Both are waterfront communities\nthat host both industries and residents"},{"time":639600,"text":"in close proximity of one another."},{"time":641510,"text":"In the post-Katrina era,\nwe have still more in common."},{"time":644582,"text":"We're at best ignored,\nand maligned and abused, at worst,"},{"time":648084,"text":"by negligent regulatory agencies,\npernicious zoning"},{"time":651455,"text":"and lax governmental accountability."},{"time":653652,"text":"Neither the destruction of the Ninth Ward\nnor the South Bronx was inevitable."},{"time":658104,"text":"But we have emerged with valuable lessons"},{"time":660264,"text":"about how to dig ourselves out."},{"time":662561,"text":"We are more than simply\nnational symbols of urban blight"},{"time":666387,"text":"or problems to be solved\nby empty campaign promises"},{"time":669717,"text":"of presidents come and gone."},{"time":671351,"text":"Now will we let the Gulf Coast\nlanguish for a decade or two,"},{"time":674194,"text":"like the South Bronx did?"},{"time":675480,"text":"Or will we take proactive steps"},{"time":676988,"text":"and learn from the homegrown resource\nof grassroots activists"},{"time":679949,"text":"that have been born of desperation\nin communities like mine?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":682819,"text":"Now listen, I do not expect individuals,"},{"time":685486,"text":"corporations or government\nto make the world a better place"},{"time":688295,"text":"because it is right or moral."},{"time":690596,"text":"This presentation today only represents\nsome of what I've been through."},{"time":694900,"text":"Like a tiny little bit. You've no clue."},{"time":697000,"text":"But I'll tell you later,\nif you want to know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":700209,"text":"But -- I know it's the bottom line,\nor one's perception of it,"},{"time":704523,"text":"that motivates people in the end."},{"time":706283,"text":"I'm interested in what I like to call\nthe \"triple bottom line\""},{"time":709229,"text":"that sustainable development can produce."},{"time":711477,"text":"Developments that have the potential\nto create positive returns"},{"time":715423,"text":"for all concerned:\nthe developers, government"},{"time":718549,"text":"and the community\nwhere these projects go up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721009,"text":"At present, that's not happening\nin New York City."},{"time":724311,"text":"And we are operating with a comprehensive\nurban-planning deficit."},{"time":728358,"text":"A parade of government subsidies"},{"time":730477,"text":"is going to propose big-box and stadium\ndevelopments in the South Bronx,"},{"time":734053,"text":"but there is scant coordination\nbetween city agencies"},{"time":737160,"text":"on how to deal with the cumulative effects\nof increased traffic, pollution,"},{"time":740934,"text":"solid waste and the impacts on open space."},{"time":743483,"text":"And their approaches to local economic\nand job development are so lame"},{"time":747887,"text":"it's not even funny."},{"time":749082,"text":"Because on top of that,"},{"time":751305,"text":"the world's richest sports team\nis replacing the House That Ruth Built"},{"time":755752,"text":"by destroying two\nwell-loved community parks."},{"time":758593,"text":"Now, we'll have even less\nthan that stat I told you about earlier."},{"time":761728,"text":"And although less than 25 percent\nof South Bronx residents own cars,"},{"time":765070,"text":"these projects include\nthousands of new parking spaces,"},{"time":768768,"text":"yet zip in terms of mass public transit."},{"time":772046,"text":"Now, what's missing from the larger debate"},{"time":774102,"text":"is a comprehensive cost-benefit analysis"},{"time":776055,"text":"between not fixing an unhealthy,\nenvironmentally-challenged community,"},{"time":779478,"text":"versus incorporating structural,\nsustainable changes."},{"time":783109,"text":"My agency is working closely\nwith Columbia University and others"},{"time":786364,"text":"to shine a light on these issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787974,"text":"Now let's get this straight:\nI am not anti-development."},{"time":791197,"text":"Ours is a city, not a wilderness preserve."},{"time":793629,"text":"And I've embraced my inner capitalist."},{"time":796692,"text":"And, but I don't have --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798193,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":799842,"text":"You probably all have,\nand if you haven't, you need to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802462,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":806256,"text":"So I don't have a problem\nwith developers making money."},{"time":809696,"text":"There's enough precedent out there\nto show that a sustainable,"},{"time":812670,"text":"community-friendly development\ncan still make a fortune."},{"time":817085,"text":"Fellow TEDsters Bill McDonough\nand Amory Lovins --"},{"time":820181,"text":"both heroes of mine by the way --\nhave shown that you can actually do that."},{"time":824174,"text":"I do have a problem\nwith developments that hyper-exploit"},{"time":827000,"text":"politically vulnerable\ncommunities for profit."},{"time":829191,"text":"That it continues is a shame upon us all,"},{"time":832063,"text":"because we are all responsible\nfor the future that we create."},{"time":835028,"text":"But one of the things I do\nto remind myself of greater possibilities,"},{"time":838299,"text":"is to learn from visionaries\nin other cities."},{"time":840457,"text":"This is my version of globalization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842513,"text":"Let's take Bogota."},{"time":844070,"text":"Poor, Latino, surrounded by\nrunaway gun violence and drug trafficking;"},{"time":847887,"text":"a reputation not unlike\nthat of the South Bronx."},{"time":850749,"text":"However, this city was blessed\nin the late 1990s"},{"time":854000,"text":"with a highly-influential\nmayor named Enrique Peñalosa."},{"time":858048,"text":"He looked at the demographics."},{"time":859853,"text":"Few Bogotanos own cars,"},{"time":861608,"text":"yet a huge portion of the city's resources\nwas dedicated to serving them."},{"time":865670,"text":"If you're a mayor, you can\ndo something about that."},{"time":868079,"text":"His administration narrowed key municipal\nthoroughfares from five lanes to three,"},{"time":872359,"text":"outlawed parking on those streets,"},{"time":874646,"text":"expanded pedestrian walkways\nand bike lanes,"},{"time":877449,"text":"created public plazas,"},{"time":879404,"text":"created one of the most efficient\nbus mass-transit systems"},{"time":882295,"text":"in the entire world."},{"time":883801,"text":"For his brilliant efforts,\nhe was nearly impeached."},{"time":888186,"text":"But as people began to see\nthat they were being put first"},{"time":891916,"text":"on issues reflecting\ntheir day-to-day lives,"},{"time":894150,"text":"incredible things happened."},{"time":895505,"text":"People stopped littering."},{"time":896921,"text":"Crime rates dropped, because the streets\nwere alive with people."},{"time":900830,"text":"His administration attacked several\ntypical urban problems at one time,"},{"time":904733,"text":"and on a third-world budget, at that."},{"time":906868,"text":"We have no excuse\nin this country, I'm sorry."},{"time":909591,"text":"But the bottom line is:\ntheir people-first agenda"},{"time":912456,"text":"was not meant to penalize\nthose who could actually afford cars,"},{"time":916394,"text":"but rather, to provide opportunities\nfor all Bogotanos to participate"},{"time":920283,"text":"in the city's resurgence."},{"time":921929,"text":"That development should not come"},{"time":924113,"text":"at the expense of the majority\nof the population"},{"time":926724,"text":"is still considered\na radical idea here in the U.S."},{"time":929518,"text":"But Bogota's example\nhas the power to change that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932327,"text":"You, however, are blessed\nwith the gift of influence."},{"time":935844,"text":"That's why you're here and why you\nvalue the information we exchange."},{"time":939590,"text":"Use your influence"},{"time":940964,"text":"in support of comprehensive,\nsustainable change everywhere."},{"time":944567,"text":"Don't just talk about it at TED."},{"time":946985,"text":"This is a nationwide policy agenda\nI'm trying to build,"},{"time":951119,"text":"and as you all know,\npolitics are personal."},{"time":954118,"text":"Help me make green the new black."},{"time":956592,"text":"Help me make sustainability sexy."},{"time":958753,"text":"Make it a part of your dinner\nand cocktail conversations."},{"time":962174,"text":"Help me fight for environmental\nand economic justice."},{"time":965301,"text":"Support investments\nwith a triple-bottom-line return."},{"time":968000,"text":"Help me democratize sustainability\nby bringing everyone to the table,"},{"time":972564,"text":"and insisting that comprehensive\nplanning can be addressed everywhere."},{"time":975937,"text":"Oh good, glad I have a little more time!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":977869,"text":"Listen -- when I spoke to Mr. Gore\nthe other day after breakfast,"},{"time":981838,"text":"I asked him how environmental justice\nactivists were going to be included"},{"time":986610,"text":"in his new marketing strategy."},{"time":988860,"text":"His response was a grant program."},{"time":992692,"text":"I don't think he understood\nthat I wasn't asking for funding."},{"time":998736,"text":"I was making him an offer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002233,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009983,"text":"What troubled me was that this\ntop-down approach is still around."},{"time":1015260,"text":"Now, don't get me wrong, we need money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017174,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018610,"text":"But grassroots groups\nare needed at the table"},{"time":1022741,"text":"during the decision-making process."},{"time":1025583,"text":"Of the 90 percent of the energy\nthat Mr. Gore reminded us"},{"time":1029651,"text":"that we waste every day,"},{"time":1031097,"text":"don't add wasting our energy, intelligence"},{"time":1034291,"text":"and hard-earned experience to that count."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1038158,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043645,"text":"I have come from so far\nto meet you like this."},{"time":1051436,"text":"Please don't waste me."},{"time":1055628,"text":"By working together,"},{"time":1056806,"text":"we can become one of those small,\nrapidly-growing groups of individuals"},{"time":1061808,"text":"who actually have the audacity and courage"},{"time":1064039,"text":"to believe that we actually\ncan change the world."},{"time":1067238,"text":"We might have come to this conference"},{"time":1069032,"text":"from very, very different\nstations in life,"},{"time":1071588,"text":"but believe me, we all share\none incredibly powerful thing."},{"time":1078517,"text":"We have nothing to lose\nand everything to gain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083675,"text":"Ciao, bellos!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1084875,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}